---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="GhanaScope: Ghana Business Intelligence for Investors and Founders"
  description="Evidence-grounded business intelligence on Ghana's economy, sectors, and investment landscape. For diaspora investors, founders, analysts, and policy professionals."
  keywords="Ghana business intelligence, diaspora investment Ghana, Ghana economy 2026, Ghana sector analysis, GIPC, cedi exchange rate"
>
  <!-- HERO -->
  <div class="hero">
    <div class="hero-inner">
      <div class="hero-label">Ghana Business Intelligence</div>
      <h1>Rigorous analysis of Ghana's economy, sectors, and investment landscape</h1>
      <p>Built for investors, founders, and analysts who need evidence, not optimism. Every claim sourced. Every risk named. Every cycle updated.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- MACRO STRIP -->
  <div class="macro-strip">
    <div class="macro-strip-inner">
      <div class="macro-item">
        <span class="macro-label">GDP Growth</span>
        <span class="macro-value positive">6.0%</span>
        <span class="macro-change">2025 confirmed</span>
      </div>
      <div class="macro-item">
        <span class="macro-label">Inflation</span>
        <span class="macro-value positive">3.3%</span>
        <span class="macro-change">Feb 2026, lowest since 1999</span>
      </div>
      <div class="macro-item">
        <span class="macro-label">USD/GHS</span>
        <span class="macro-value negative">10.97</span>
        <span class="macro-change">+29% YoY depreciation</span>
      </div>
      <div class="macro-item">
        <span class="macro-label">Policy Rate</span>
        <span class="macro-value">14.0%</span>
        <span class="macro-change">Cut 150bps, Mar 18</span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="macro-source">Sources: Ghana Statistical Service, Bank of Ghana, NPA. Data as of March 2026.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="container">
    <!-- LATEST ANALYSIS -->
    <div class="section reveal">
      <div class="section-header">
        <div class="section-label">Latest Analysis</div>
        <div class="section-title">Published Reports</div>
      </div>

      <div class="card-grid">
        <a href="/analysis/gse-crash-2026" class="article-card">
          <span class="card-tag risk">Risk Alert</span>
          <h3>GSE Crash: From 15,000 to 12,990 in One Week</h3>
          <p>The Ghana Stock Exchange hit a record 15,185 then lost 14% in days. T-bill compression, search-for-yield exhaustion, thin market structure, and the cocoa question. Four scenarios with indicator watchlist.</p>
          <div class="card-meta">
            <span>March 29, 2026</span>
            <span>8 min read</span>
            <span>Capital Markets</span>
          </div>
        </a>

        <a href="/analysis/hormuz-crisis-ghana-2026" class="article-card">
          <span class="card-tag risk">Risk Alert</span>
          <h3>Hormuz Crisis: How $114 Oil Reaches a Ghanaian Market Stall</h3>
          <p>Diesel up 25.7% in one NPA window. Four transmission channels traced from the Strait of Hormuz to Ghana's fuel pumps, transport costs, generators, and imported goods.</p>
          <div class="card-meta">
            <span>March 28, 2026</span>
            <span>12 min read</span>
            <span>Macro / Global</span>
          </div>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- PIPELINE -->
    <div class="section reveal">
      <div class="section-header">
        <div class="section-label">In Development</div>
        <div class="section-title">Advancing Through Editorial Pipeline</div>
        <div class="section-desc">Each report passes 8 stages with 3 mandatory quality gates. Fact-checked by 5 specialist agents. Nothing publishes without evidence.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="card-grid">
        <div class="article-card" style="opacity:0.65;">
          <span class="card-tag policy">Policy</span>
          <h3>BoG Rate Cut to 14%: What the 3-1-1 Vote Means</h3>
          <p>Three for 150bps, one for 75bps, one to hold. The May MPC is now the most consequential monetary policy moment of 2026.</p>
          <div class="card-meta">
            <span class="status-badge">Stage 1 of 8</span>
            <span>Monetary Policy</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="article-card" style="opacity:0.65;">
          <span class="card-tag scenario">Scenario</span>
          <h3>Ghana's Triple Shock: Three Scenarios for 2026</h3>
          <p>Hormuz, cocoa crisis, and GSE correction converge. Base case, upside, downside, and wildcard with probability estimates and indicator watchlists.</p>
          <div class="card-meta">
            <span class="status-badge">Stage 1 of 8</span>
            <span>Macro Scenario</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- COVERAGE -->
    <div class="section reveal">
      <div class="section-header">
        <div class="section-label">Coverage</div>
        <div class="section-title">What We Analyze</div>
      </div>

      <div class="card-grid cols-3">
        <div class="grid-card">
          <h3>Sector Analysis</h3>
          <p>Agriculture, fintech, real estate, healthcare, logistics. Ghana-specific market sizing, competitive dynamics, and infrastructure constraints.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="grid-card">
          <h3>Diaspora Execution</h3>
          <p>GIPC registration, fraud prevention, remote-viable businesses, trust mechanisms. What works and what kills diaspora ventures.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="grid-card">
          <h3>Scenario Modeling</h3>
          <p>3-5 possible futures with probability estimates. Observable indicators. What breaks the thesis. Updated each cycle.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="grid-card">
          <h3>Risk Assessment</h3>
          <p>Currency, political, infrastructure, counterparty, and operational risk. Every opportunity includes what kills it.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="grid-card">
          <h3>Policy Tracking</h3>
          <p>BoG decisions, GIPC reforms, fiscal policy, trade agreements. Impact analysis, not summaries.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="grid-card">
          <h3>Opportunity Scoring</h3>
          <p>Weighted composite scoring across market size, infrastructure, execution feasibility, currency risk, and diaspora fit.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- TRUST STRIP -->
  <div class="trust-strip reveal">
    <div class="trust-strip-inner">
      <div class="trust-item">
        <div class="trust-value">25</div>
        <div class="trust-label">Analytical agents across 6 divisions</div>
      </div>
      <div class="trust-item">
        <div class="trust-value">8</div>
        <div class="trust-label">Publishing stages per report</div>
      </div>
      <div class="trust-item">
        <div class="trust-value">3</div>
        <div class="trust-label">Mandatory quality gates</div>
      </div>
      <div class="trust-item">
        <div class="trust-value">0</div>
        <div class="trust-label">Reports published without fact-check</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="container">
    <!-- METHODOLOGY -->
    <div class="section reveal">
      <div class="section-header">
        <div class="section-label">Methodology</div>
        <div class="section-title">How We Work</div>
        <div class="section-desc">GhanaScope is powered by GhanaWorld, a multi-agent intelligence system. Every cycle ingests fresh data, runs sector analysis, scores opportunities, and enforces quality standards.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="card-grid cols-2">
        <div class="grid-card">
          <h3>Source Protocol</h3>
          <p>Every factual claim mapped to a source: official data, verified news, web-fresh research, or model inference. Confidence levels stated explicitly.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="grid-card">
          <h3>Enforcement</h3>
          <p>Independent enforcement division scans all outputs for hallucination, risk suppression, false completeness, and unsupported optimism. Veto power over any report.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="grid-card">
          <h3>Ghana-Specificity</h3>
          <p>No generic "emerging market" frameworks. Every analysis cites Ghana-specific evidence, constraints, and context. Regional comparisons name the country and the difference.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="grid-card">
          <h3>Known Unknowns</h3>
          <p>We track what we don't know. Gaps are logged, not hidden. If the data doesn't exist, we say so. False completeness is a violation.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- WHO THIS IS FOR -->
    <div class="section reveal">
      <div class="section-header">
        <div class="section-label">Audience</div>
        <div class="section-title">Built for Serious Decision-Makers</div>
      </div>

      <div class="card-grid cols-2">
        <div class="grid-card">
          <h3>Diaspora Investors</h3>
          <p>Evaluating opportunities in Ghana from abroad. Need honest risk assessment, execution barriers, and remote-viability analysis.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="grid-card">
          <h3>Founders and Operators</h3>
          <p>Building or running businesses in Ghana. Need market sizing, competitive dynamics, unit economics, and infrastructure reality.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="grid-card">
          <h3>Institutional Analysts</h3>
          <p>DFIs, PE/VC, research teams. Need structured data, scenario models, and sector intelligence with stated confidence levels.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="grid-card">
          <h3>Policy Professionals</h3>
          <p>Tracking Ghana's regulatory and macroeconomic environment. Need impact analysis, not press release summaries.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <div class="cta-strip reveal">
    <h2>Intelligence delivered to your inbox</h2>
    <p>New reports, risk alerts, and scenario updates. No hype. No spam.</p>
    <form class="cta-form" id="newsletter-form">
      <input type="email" name="email" placeholder="your@email.com" required class="cta-input" aria-label="Email address" />
      <button type="submit" class="cta-button">Subscribe</button>
    </form>
    <p class="cta-note" id="newsletter-status">Free. Unsubscribe anytime.</p>
  </div>

  <script>
    const form = document.getElementById('newsletter-form');
    const status = document.getElementById('newsletter-status');
    if (form && status) {
      form.addEventListener('submit', (e) => {
        e.preventDefault();
        const input = form.querySelector('input[name="email"]') as HTMLInputElement;
        const email = input?.value;
        if (!email) return;
        const subs = JSON.parse(localStorage.getItem('ghanascope_subscribers') || '[]');
        if (subs.includes(email)) {
          status.textContent = 'Already subscribed.';
          status.style.color = '#C9A84C';
          return;
        }
        subs.push(email);
        localStorage.setItem('ghanascope_subscribers', JSON.stringify(subs));
        status.textContent = 'Subscribed. You will be notified when delivery is live.';
        status.style.color = '#2E7D32';
        input.value = '';
      });
    }
  </script>
</Base>
